response:
To configure an OIDC identity provider for an existing AWS EKS cluster named "example", we use the `aws_eks_identity_provider_config` resource. This resource allows the EKS control plane to authenticate users via an external OIDC provider (such as Okta, Google, or Keycloak).

Here is the complete Terraform configuration:

```hcl
# Standard AWS Provider configuration
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# 1. Data source to reference the existing EKS cluster by name
data "aws_eks_cluster" "example" {
  name = "example"
}

# 2. Configure the OIDC Identity Provider for the EKS cluster
# This resource links to the cluster and defines the authentication parameters
resource "aws_eks_identity_provider_config" "example" {
  cluster_name = data.aws_eks_cluster.example.name

  oidc {
    # The name for the identity provider configuration
    identity_provider_config_name = "example-oidc-config"

    # The URL of the OIDC identity provider (e.g., Okta, Google, etc.)
    issuer_url = "https://oidc.example.com"

    # The client ID for the application registered with the OIDC provider
    client_id = "example-client-id"

    # Optional: Define which claims to use for usernames and groups
    username_claim = "email"
    groups_claim   = "groups"
  }

  # Optional tags for the resource
  tags = {
    Environment = "production"
    ManagedBy   = "Terraform"
  }
}
```

