response:
To associate an existing Amazon ElastiCache user with an existing user group, we use the `aws_elasticache_user_group_association` resource. This resource allows you to manage the membership of a user within a group without needing to manage the entire user group resource definition.

We will use `data` sources to reference the existing user and user group by their respective IDs.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Reference the existing ElastiCache User
data "aws_elasticache_user" "existing_user" {
  user_id = "my-existing-user-id"
}

# Reference the existing ElastiCache User Group
data "aws_elasticache_user_group" "existing_group" {
  user_group_id = "my-existing-group-id"
}

# Associate the existing user with the existing user group
resource "aws_elasticache_user_group_association" "example" {
  user_group_id = data.aws_elasticache_user_group.existing_group.user_group_id
  user_id       = data.aws_elasticache_user.existing_user.user_id
}
```

