To create a SageMaker Human Task UI resource in AWS using Terraform, we need to use the `aws_sagemaker_human_task_ui` resource. This resource requires a unique name and a `ui_template` block which contains the HTML content used for the human review interface.

Here is the complete Terraform configuration:

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Create the SageMaker Human Task UI
resource "aws_sagemaker_human_task_ui" "example" {
  human_task_ui_name = "sagemaker-human-task-ui-template"

  ui_template {
    content = <<EOF
<h1>
    TEST
</h1>
EOF
  }
}

# Output the ARN of the created Human Task UI
output "human_task_ui_arn" {
  value       = aws_sagemaker_human_task_ui.example.arn
  description = "The Amazon Resource Name of the Human Task UI."
}
```

