response:
To create an Amazon DAX (DynamoDB Accelerator) parameter group in Terraform, we use the `aws_dax_parameter_group` resource. This resource allows you to manage the runtime settings for your DAX cluster, such as Time-to-Live (TTL) settings for queries and records.

Here is the complete Terraform configuration to create a DAX parameter group.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Create a DAX Parameter Group
# This group manages settings like TTL for the DAX cluster
resource "aws_dax_parameter_group" "example" {
  name        = "example-dax-parameter-group"
  description = "A custom parameter group for DAX to manage TTL settings"

  # Example parameter: query-ttl-millis
  # Specifies the amount of time that a query result is cached in DAX
  parameters {
    name  = "query-ttl-millis"
    value = "60000" # 60 seconds
  }

  # Example parameter: record-ttl-millis
  # Specifies the amount of time that an individual item is cached in DAX
  parameters {
    name  = "record-ttl-millis"
    value = "300000" # 5 minutes
  }
}

# Output the name of the parameter group for reference
output "dax_parameter_group_name" {
  value       = aws_dax_parameter_group.example.name
  description = "The name of the created DAX parameter group"
}
```

