To set up the requested infrastructure, I will first define a networking stack including a VPC, subnets, and security groups to isolate the database and proxy. I will then configure AWS Secrets Manager to store database credentials securely and establish an IAM role that allows the RDS Proxy to retrieve these secrets. Finally, I will provision the Aurora MySQL cluster with the specified backup retention and window settings, followed by the RDS Proxy and its target group to manage database connections efficiently.

