To set up an AWS RDS Aurora MySQL cluster with an RDS Proxy, we first establish the networking foundation by creating a VPC with private subnets across multiple availability zones. We then configure secure credential management using AWS Secrets Manager and define an IAM role that allows the RDS Proxy to access these secrets. Finally, we provision the Aurora cluster with a specified final snapshot identifier and deploy the RDS Proxy with a target group linked to the database cluster to manage connection pooling efficiently.

