response:
To create an egress-only internet gateway for IPv6 traffic in AWS, we use the `aws_egress_only_internet_gateway` resource. This resource allows instances in a VPC to communicate with the internet over IPv6 while preventing the internet from initiating a connection with those instances.

Here is the complete Terraform configuration:

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Variable to specify the existing VPC ID
variable "vpc_id" {
  type        = string
  description = "The ID of the VPC where the egress-only internet gateway will be created."
}

# Create the Egress-Only Internet Gateway
resource "aws_egress_only_internet_gateway" "pike" {
  vpc_id = var.vpc_id

  tags = {
    Name        = "pike"
    permissions = "true"
  }
}
```

