To create the requested AWS infrastructure, we will use the `aws_vpc_dhcp_options` resource to define the Google DNS settings and the `aws_vpc_dhcp_options_association` resource to link it to a VPC.

Note: In AWS, the `aws_vpc_dhcp_options_association` resource does not support metadata tagging via the API. Therefore, the "permissions" tag is applied to the DHCP Options resource itself.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Create the DHCP Options Set named "pike"
resource "aws_vpc_dhcp_options" "pike" {
  domain_name_servers = ["8.8.8.8", "8.8.4.4"]

  tags = {
    Name        = "pike"
    permissions = "true"
  }
}

# Variable to specify the existing VPC ID
variable "vpc_id" {
  type        = string
  description = "The ID of the VPC to which the DHCP options will be associated."
}

# Associate the DHCP Options with the specified VPC
# Note: AWS VPC DHCP Options Association resources do not support tags via the AWS API.
resource "aws_vpc_dhcp_options_association" "pike_association" {
  vpc_id          = var.vpc_id
  dhcp_options_id = aws_vpc_dhcp_options.pike.id
}
```

