To create the AWS DHCP options and associate them with a VPC as requested, we will use the `aws_vpc_dhcp_options` and `aws_vpc_dhcp_options_association` resources. 

Note: While the request asks to tag both the DHCP options and the association, the AWS API (and consequently the Terraform AWS Provider) does not support tags on the DHCP Options Association resource itself. I have applied the "permissions" tag to the DHCP Options resource and used a descriptive name for the association.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# Variable to define the VPC ID to which these options will be associated
variable "vpc_id" {
  description = "The ID of the VPC to associate with the DHCP options"
  type        = string
}

# Create the DHCP Options set named "pike"
resource "aws_vpc_dhcp_options" "pike" {
  domain_name_servers = ["8.8.8.8", "8.8.4.4"]

  tags = {
    Name = "pike"
    # Tagging with "permissions" as per request
    Project = "permissions"
  }
}

# Associate the DHCP Options with the specified VPC
resource "aws_vpc_dhcp_options_association" "pike_association" {
